news.title: Kalapataru Projects International raises about Rs 1,000 crore through share sale on QIP route
news.para: Kalpataru Projects International Ltd (KPIL) has raised about Rs 1,000 crore through issuance 83.26 lakh equity shares at Rs 1,201 per piece on qualified institutions placement (QIP) basis.

news.title: Indore: 31 brick kilns to be razed to make way for MR-12 road project
news.para: The Indore Development Authority (IDA) is constructing the 9.4 km long MR-12 road from the Bypass to Ujjain Road. Due to various obstacles, only 3.5 km of the road was completed so far.

news.title: Bill tabled in Karnataka assembly to replace MUDA with Mysuru development body
news.para: Unlike MUDA, which had all the legislators from Mysuru and the police commissioner as its members, the MDA will have only two legislators from Karnataka.

news.title: Sweden's SBB exchanges $2.9 billion debt, eyes lower leverage ahead
news.para: The group said bondholders had agreed to an exchange of debt valued at 2.78 billion euros ($2.92 billion) in return for new securities, part of an effort to overcome objections from some creditors to its restructuring.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet approves 30% land subsidy for multi-modal logistics parks
news.para: Officials said a company establishing a multi-modal logistics park will be given a 30% upfront land subsidy on plots leased by industrial development authorities or any state govt agency.

news.title: Sanghi Industries shares tumble nearly 13% on merger with Ambuja Cements
news.para: Adani Group will merge its recently acquired Sanghi Industries and Penna Cement with Ambuja Cements to consolidate cement operations in one unit, the conglomerate said Tuesday.

news.title: Sahiti Infratec Ventures and its promoters swindled 842 crore from homebuyers: ED
news.para: In its prosecution complaint filed in the PMLA court recently, ED alleged that the total Rs 853 crore collected, Rs 214 crore involved cash transactions with funds diverted through multiple accounts.

news.title: Indian real estate attracts $8.87 billion institutional investments in 2024: Report
news.para: In its report released on Wednesday, real estate consultant JLL India has estimated the institutional investment in Indian real estate at USD 8.878 billion in 2024 compared to USD 5.878 billion in the preceding calendar year.

news.title: Haryana CM to chair meeting on metro expansion plans
news.para: Officials said a key portion of the discussion will be on the Millennium City Centre-Cyber City line.

news.title: Rajkot: Three property owners booked for violating tenant registration rules
news.para: Legal action has been initiated against three property owners — Tariq Himani (33), Firdosh Sheikh (37), and Shailesh Patel — for failing to register their non-local tenants with the police, as mandated by the Act.

news.title: Mall culture struggles to thrive in Panchkula
news.para: At Rajhans only one commercial space, a restaurant, is occupied while remaining all other shops on ground as well as first floor could not be allotted.

news.title: Tenant cannot dictate how landlord uses property: Delhi high court
news.para: It was dealing with a plea filed by a distraught couple seeking eviction of a tenant living in a portion of the premises.

news.title: Karnataka high court rejects objection to landowners' development plans
news.para: Mahaveer and Anil had approached the Vijayapura Urban Development Authority, seeking approval for the plan of a layout they wanted to develop on their lands

news.title: MCG demolishes 20 illegal structures to reclaim seven acres in Gurugram
news.para: The freed land, worth crores of rupees, is part of a residential zone, allowing both residential and commercial development.

news.title: Kochi: KCZMA issues guidelines to local bodies on dwelling unit permits
news.para: The govt order (GO) dated Dec 6, 2024, stated that local self-govt institutions can grant permission for residential constructions up to 300 sq m in areas classified as CRZ II, CRZ III A and CRZ III B, subject to conditions as per the 2019 CRZ notification.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 451 properties in crackdown on property tax defaulters
news.para: ​​The sealed properties include residential and non-residential units in various wards, including Rakhiyal, Khokhra, Nikol and Odhav.

news.title: Lucknow development body to begin plot registration for Mohan Road scheme
news.para: During a site inspection on Tuesday, LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar directed officials to accelerate development work by increasing machinery and workforce deployment.

news.title: ADB to provide Rs 1,527 crore aid for phase-II of Nagpur metro project
news.para: MahaMetro managing director Shravan Hardikar and ADB director Mio Oka signed the MoU in the presence of Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis in the cabinet hall of the Vidhan Bhavan.

news.title: Ambuja Cements to merge Sanghi Industries and Penna Cement with itself
news.para: Ambuja Cements will issue 12 equity shares of the face value of Rs 2 each for every 100 equity shares of Sanghi Industries of face value Rs. 10 each.

news.title: Sebi orders forensic audit of TARC's financial statements
news.para: TARC said that it shall provide all necessary information, assistance and cooperation concerning the forensic audit and shall inform the exchanges of any further developments in the matter.
